<subSubSection id="C30165293306FFC224C18F5BFF2CFA1B" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA436A23306FFC224C18F5BFF2CFA1B" blockId="5.[151,1437,510,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC224C18F5BFEF8FD02" bold="true" box="[199,314,618,644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The forewing length is 
<quantity id="4CE39B473306FFC2264E8F5AFD02FD03" box="[584,704,619,645]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11–12 mm</quantity>
in males and 
<quantity id="4CE39B473306FFC227518F5AFC0DFD03" box="[855,975,619,645]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14 mm</quantity>
in females. The new species (
<figureCitation id="13202A273306FFC2211F8F5AFAB9FD03" box="[1305,1403,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[198,1393,183,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-26@7.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Marcinistra gen. n. and Baimistra gen. n. spp.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 1 and 2 in HNHM; 3–6 in AFM; 7 and 8 in ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6593182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6593182/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
) is externally similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC2257B8FBEFDCBFD2F" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[381,521,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC2257B8FBEFDCBFD2F" box="[381,521,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13202A273306FFC226118FBEFDBBFD2F" box="[535,633,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[198,1393,183,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-26@7.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Marcinistra gen. n. and Baimistra gen. n. spp.: adults. Depositories of the specimens: 1 and 2 in HNHM; 3–6 in AFM; 7 and 8 in ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6593182" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6593182/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) but is distinguished by the smaller size, the more intense metallic green suffusion on the forewing, and the paler brown dash outward from the reniform stigma. Compared to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC2212B8F82FF03FD77" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC2212B8F82FF03FD77" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13202A273306FFC224D78FE6FEE1FD77" box="[209,291,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[168,1432,185,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-26@11.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Marcinistra gen. n. and Baimistra gen. n. spp.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 21 in HNHM; 22 and 23 in AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6593190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6593190/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), the male genital capsule of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC2266A8FE6FD29FD77" authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[620,747,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leichina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC2266A8FE6FD29FD77" box="[620,747,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. leichina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC226F48FE6FCF0FD77" bold="true" box="[754,818,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C57CB3306FFC226F48FE6FCF0FD77" box="[754,818,727,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13202A273306FFC227478FE6FC50FD77" box="[833,914,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[168,1432,185,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-26@11.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Marcinistra gen. n. and Baimistra gen. n. spp.: male genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 21 in HNHM; 22 and 23 in AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6593190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6593190/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) has a somewhat narrower juxta with a deeper medial depression and a larger swollen ventral process. The valva of the new species is basally broader than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC221788FCAFF3DFCBF" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC221788FCAFF3DFCBF" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, more down curved distally, and has a broader apex and an extremely short ventral subapical protrusion. The harpe of the new species has a broader base than in the congener and is only slightly apically dilated whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC224918E56FEE6FC07" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[151,292,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC224918E56FEE6FC07" box="[151,292,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is arrowhead-like dilated subapically and bears a short triangular dorsal protrusion. The sacculus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC224918EBAFED4FC23" authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,278,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leichina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC224918EBAFED4FC23" box="[151,278,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. leichina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC2251A8EBAFE99FC23" bold="true" box="[284,347,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C57CB3306FFC2251A8EBAFE99FC23" box="[284,347,907,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a slightly larger distal process and a prominent, lobe-like clavus whereas the clavus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC221488EBAFF1DFC4F" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC221488EBAFF1DFC4F" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very short but broad and only slightly protrudes from the sacculus surface. The phallus of the new species is somewhat shorter than in the congener (in proportion to the length of the tegumen-uncus complex), slightly more down curved, bears a somewhat larger lateral thorn-like carinal process and lacks a dorsal dentate carinal plate. The vesicae of the two species are similar but that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC226B6892AFCEDFBB3" authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[688,815,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leichina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC226B6892AFCEDFBB3" box="[688,815,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. leichina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC22733892AFCB6FBB3" bold="true" box="[821,884,1051,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C57CB3306FFC22733892AFCB6FBB3" box="[821,884,1051,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is somewhat basally broader than in the congener and has a smaller distal diverticulum. In the female genitalia of the new species (
<figureCitation id="13202A273306FFC22032890EFB4AFBDF" box="[1076,1160,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,182,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Marcinistra gen. n., Baimistra gen. n. and Conistra spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 30 and 34 in HNHM; 31 in AFM; 32 and 33 in ZSM; 35 in BBT." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6593198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6593198/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
), the apophyses are apically narrower than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC225948952FDDCFBFB" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[402,542,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC225948952FDDCFBFB" box="[402,542,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13202A273306FFC2262B8952FD42FBFB" box="[557,640,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[166,1415,182,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-18@14.[151,1435,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Marcinistra gen. n., Baimistra gen. n. and Conistra spp.: female genitalia. Depositories of the specimens dissected: 30 and 34 in HNHM; 31 in AFM; 32 and 33 in ZSM; 35 in BBT." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6593198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6593198/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), and the apophysis posterioris is somewhat longer (in proportion to the length of the apophysis anterioris). The antrum of the new species is narrower than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC2206E89B6FB34FB27" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[1128,1270,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC2206E89B6FB34FB27" box="[1128,1270,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has markedly longer and broader ventral postero-lateral subostial lobes and a rugose ventral surface between them (whereas it is smooth in the congener). The ductus bursae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC226AC89FEFCE8FB6F" authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[682,810,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leichina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC226AC89FEFCE8FB6F" box="[682,810,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. leichina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC2273489FEFCB0FB6F" bold="true" box="[818,882,1231,1257]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C57CB3306FFC2273489FEFCB0FB6F" box="[818,882,1231,1257]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is somewhat longer than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC220B789FEFAFDFB6F" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[1201,1343,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC220B789FEFAFDFB6F" box="[1201,1343,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has a broader and anteriorly straight lateral sclerotised plate whereas it is anteriorly curved and reaching the base of the appendix bursae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC225778826FE3DFAB7" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[369,511,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC225778826FE3DFAB7" box="[369,511,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The corpus bursae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC226F98826FCBCFAB7" authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[767,894,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leichina" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC226F98826FCBCFAB7" box="[767,894,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. leichina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC227838826FC06FAB7" bold="true" box="[901,964,1303,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C57CB3306FFC227838826FC06FAB7" box="[901,964,1303,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is conspicuously shorter and broader than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC224B2880AFE83FAD3" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[180,321,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC224B2880AFE83FAD3" box="[180,321,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and bears only one small signum whereas that of the congener bears four larger signa. Additionally, the appendix bursae of the new species is somewhat narrower than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213306FFC227A6886EFBEFFAFF" authorityName="Hreblay &amp; L. Ronkay" authorityYear="1998" box="[928,1069,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Marcinistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC227A6886EFBEFFAFF" box="[928,1069,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">M. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has a more constricted basal section.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30165293306FFC224C18897FA5FFA47" box="[199,1437,1446,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA436A23306FFC224C18897FA5FFA47" blockId="5.[151,1437,510,1581]" box="[199,1437,1446,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC224C18897FE9BFA46" bold="true" box="[199,345,1446,1472]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Distribution</emphasis>
. The new species is known only from its 
<typeStatus id="54A088003306FFC227258896FC91FA47" box="[803,851,1447,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">type</typeStatus>
locality in north-western 
<collectingRegion id="49DFF8403306FFC220768896FAEDFA47" box="[1136,1327,1447,1473]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
of 
<collectingCountry id="F30C76323306FFC221548896FA5BFA47" box="[1362,1433,1447,1473]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30165293306FFC224C188FAFE60F9AB" pageId="5" pageNumber="447" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA436A23306FFC224C188FAFE60F9AB" blockId="5.[151,1437,510,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03306FFC224C188FAFE8CFA63" bold="true" box="[199,334,1483,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="447">Etymology.</emphasis>
‘Leichina’ is a Latin transliteration of the Greek word ‘λειχήνα’ meaning ‘lichen’. The specific epithet refers to the diffuse shiny green spots and suffusion on the forewing reminiscent of certain groups of lichens. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
